  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='client_id' href='#client_id'></a> client_id</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The OAuth client id (get from <a href="https://account.withings.com/partner/add_oauth2">https://account.withings.com/partner/add_oauth2</a>)</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='client_secret' href='#client_secret'></a> client_secret</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The OAuth secret (get from <a href="https://account.withings.com/partner/add_oauth2">https://account.withings.com/partner/add_oauth2</a>)</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='profiles' href='#profiles'></a> profiles</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='map'>map</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>Withings supports multiple profiles per account. Provide the person‚Äôs name whom you want Home Assistant entities to will be associated with (just a name, it doesn‚Äôt have to be perfect). During the authorization step, you will be asked to select this user from the Withings website.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
